%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20the%20age%20of%20AI%2C%20there's%20no%20future%20for%20workers%20content%20with%20being%20code%20monkeys%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they%20know%20it%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20snail%20in%20front%20of%20a%20computer%20with%20a%20red%20%26quot%3Bno%26quot%3B%20symbol%20on%20the%20screen%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a7f107a0fc5856d59860ae%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EiStock%3B%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EArtificial%20intelligence%20is%20now%20the%20top%20priority%20for%20major%20tech%20firms.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESoftware%20engineers%20know%20they%20need%20to%20do%20more%20than%20just%20code%20to%20stay%20relevant%20in%20the%20AI%20era.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20the%20way%20forward%20isn't%20to%20push%20back%20against%20AI%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20to%20embrace%20it%2C%20they%20tell%20BI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESoftware%20engineers%20know%20that%20the%20days%20of%20simply%20being%20able%20to%20code%20are%20behind%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20artificial%20intelligence%20taking%20over%20jobs%20is%20not%20new%20%E2%80%94%20numerous%20tech%20giants%20over%20the%20past%20two%20years%20announced%20that%20they%20were%20axing%20jobs%20to%20focus%20more%20on%20artificial%20intelligence%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Google%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-layoffs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslashed%2012%2C000%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%206%25%20of%20its%20then%20workforce%20%E2%80%94%20as%20the%20company%20began%20shifting%20its%20priorities%20toward%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%202023%2C%20IBM%20announced%20that%20it%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdropbox-ibm-google-big-tech-companies-ai-in-layoff-memos-2023-5%23ibm-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epause%20hiring%20for%20roles%20that%20could%20be%20replaced%20by%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20affected%20roles%2C%20which%20amounted%20to%2026%2C000%20jobs%2C%20included%20those%20in%20human%20resources%20and%20other%20non-consumer-facing%20departments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20AI%20has%20had%20a%20direct%20impact%20on%20software%20engineers%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20AI%20has%20helped%20to%20increase%20their%20productivity%20by%20helping%20to%20debug%20and%20generate%20code%2C%20software%20engineers%20that%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20to%20said%20that%20they%20expect%20the%20industry%20to%20shrink%20simply%20because%20it%20doesn't%20need%20as%20many%20workers%20as%20they%20do%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20they%20said%2C%20means%20they%20have%20to%20work%20smarter%20if%20they%20want%20to%20keep%20their%20jobs.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2246fa40b7-28ed-4cdd-8b6b-706f096a4034%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAI%20will%20push%20companies%20to%20have%20leaner%20software%20engineering%20teams%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EArpita%20Kaushik%2C%20a%20data%20scientist%20at%20Rocket%20Mortgage%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20AI%20tools%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fchat-gpt%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcodex-github-copilot-chatgpt-openai-productivity-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGithub%20Copilot%3C%2Fa%3E%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bheavy%20lifting%26quot%3B%20for%20workers%20like%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20meant%20that%20companies%20could%20get%20by%20with%20leaner%20teams%20without%20compromising%20on%20output%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20there%20will%20be%20a%20change%20in%20the%20way%20a%20software%20engineer%20works%2C%20and%20instead%20of%20five%20software%20engineers%20you%20might%20need%20four%20in%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKaushik's%20point%20was%20echoed%20by%20Aditya%20Swami%2C%20who%20heads%20product%20development%20efforts%20at%20Hatcher%2B%2C%20a%20venture%20capital%20firm%20in%20Singapore.%20In%20fact%2C%20Swami%20said%20that%20shrinking%20headcounts%20will%20be%20even%20more%20apparent%20in%20bigger%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20going%20to%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAs%20an%20industry%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20shrink%2C%20and%20only%20people%20who%20really%20understand%20what%20they're%20doing%20are%20going%20to%20survive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221744%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Aditya%20Swami%2C%20the%20head%20of%20product%20development%20at%20Hatcher%2B%2C%20a%20venture%20capital%20firm%20in%20Singapore.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a84d3aaab37011780b8663%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221308%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAditya%20Swami%2C%20the%20head%20of%20product%20development%20at%20Hatcher%2B%2C%20a%20venture%20capital%20firm%20in%20Singapore.%3Cp%3EAditya%20Swami%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20problem%20isn't%20just%20about%20there%20being%20fewer%20jobs%20available.%20Kaushik%20said%20the%20rise%20of%20AI%20means%20that%20the%20bar%20for%20hiring%20is%20much%20higher%20now%20for%20interns%20and%20entry-level%20software%20engineers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20people%20have%20to%20stretch%20their%20limits%3B%20they%20have%20to%20do%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20senior-level%20roles%20even%20at%20the%20starting%20of%20their%20careers%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20the%20basic%20things%20they%20could%20do%2C%20now%20they%20could%20do%20with%20AI.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224a757fb3-2ca9-47b0-9289-f9f9d5df76dc%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20say%20goodbye%20to%20technical%20skills%20just%20yet%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20software%20engineers%20who%20think%20they%20can%20rely%20on%20AI%20to%20solve%20their%20problems%20may%20be%20disappointed%20to%20learn%20that%20one's%20technical%20abilities%20still%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESwami%20from%20Hatcher%2B%20said%20that%20he%20still%20expects%20his%20engineers%20to%20have%20strong%20coding%20skills%2C%20be%20able%20to%20understand%20code%20and%20explain%20what%20they%20are%20doing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20people%20who%20studied%20software%20engineering%20before%20the%20rise%20of%20AI%20tools%20have%20a%20stronger%20foundation%20because%20they%20have%20%26quot%3Bwritten%20code%20from%20scratch.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20biggest%20problem%20right%20now%20is%20that%20the%20AI%20large%20language%20model%20hallucinates.%20It's%20not%20correct%20100%25%2C%20only%2050%20to%2060%25%20of%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20still%20need%20to%20be%20very%20careful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20an%20interview%2C%20you%20should%20be%20able%20to%20explain%20line%20by%20line%20what%20the%20code%20is%20doing.%20That's%20still%20very%20important%2C%20that%20hasn't%20changed%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdrian%20Goh%2C%20cofounder%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nodeflair.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENodeFlair%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20job%20board%20for%20tech%20professionals%20in%20Asia%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20one's%20technical%20foundations%20have%20only%20become%20more%20important%20in%20the%20age%20of%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompanies%20value%20engineers%20with%20strong%20fundamentals%20who%20are%20dedicated%20to%20continuous%20learning%20and%20self-upgrading.%20These%20qualities%20ensure%20adaptability%20to%20evolving%20roles%20and%20technologies%2C%26quot%3B%20Goh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22191cb370-2c56-496c-853d-944ad10d0412%5C%22%3EA%20computer%20science%20degree%20is%20still%20far%20from%20useless%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAcademics%20BI%20spoke%20to%20also%20said%20the%20rise%20of%20AI%20has%20not%20diminished%20the%20value%20of%20a%20computer%20science%20degree%20and%20the%20technical%20skills%20that%20come%20with%20earning%20it%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BComputer%20science%20is%20not%20just%20about%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.comp.nus.edu.sg%2F~kanmy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKan%20Min%20Yen%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20computer%20science%20at%20the%20National%20University%20of%20Singapore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BProper%20development%20and%20use%20of%20AI%20still%20require%20fundamental%20knowledge%20of%20software%20engineering%2C%20data%20management%2C%20and%20security%2C%20all%20tenets%20of%20a%20holistic%20computing%20education%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20may%20think%20that%20tools%20like%20GitHub%20Copilot%20will%20render%20them%20obsolete%2C%20Kan%20said%20such%20concerns%20may%20be%20overblown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoftware%20professionals%2C%20he%20said%2C%20could%20still%20add%20value%20by%20understanding%20the%20limitations%20of%20AI%20tools%20and%20how%20to%20troubleshoot%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20would%20go%20to%20a%20mechanic%20to%20fix%20a%20car%20and%20to%20someone%20who%20knows%20the%20math%20and%20training%20methods%20for%20large%20language%20modules%20to%20fix%20and%20diagnose%20problems%20with%20LLMs%2C%20such%20as%20ChatGPT%2C%26quot%3B%20Kan%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdr.ntu.edu.sg%2Fcris%2Frp%2Frp00698%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBo%20An%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20heads%20the%20AI%20division%20at%20Singapore's%20Nanyang%20Technological%20University%20(NTU)%2C%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20core%20value%20of%20a%20CS%20degree%20remains%20robust%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20advancements%20in%20AI%20do%20not%20erode%20the%20value%20of%20a%20CS%20degree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20added%20that%20foundational%20knowledge%20in%20%26quot%3Balgorithms%2C%20data%20structures%2C%20software%20engineering%2C%20and%20other%20critical%20areas%26quot%3B%20is%20essential%20for%20advancing%20AI%20technologies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ed831ea3-0022-49b8-bcaa-0e5519f42de1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAspiring%20software%20engineers%20need%20to%20embrace%20AI%20and%20work%20on%20their%20own%20projects%20to%20stay%20ahead%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20software%20engineers%20looking%20to%20score%20a%20job%20in%20software%20engineering%20must%20strike%20a%20tricky%20balance%20between%20integrating%20AI%20into%20their%20workflows%20and%20honing%20their%20fundamentals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-computer-science-professor-prisoners-use-phones-cs50-free-class-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDavid%20Malan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20computer%20science%20professor%20at%20Harvard%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20AI%20tools%20could%20be%20a%20plus%20for%20aspiring%20software%20engineers%20who%20know%20how%20to%20leverage%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20near%20term%2C%20AI%20is%20posed%20to%20amplify%20the%20impact%20of%20individual%20software%20engineers%2C%26quot%3B%20Malan%20said.%20%26quot%3BConsider%20just%20how%20many%20more%20features%20they%20can%20implement%2C%20how%20many%20more%20bugs%20they%20can%20fix%20if%20they%20have%20a%20virtual%20assistant%20by%20their%20side.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMalan%20also%20advised%20job%20seekers%20to%20continue%20building%20up%20their%20portfolio%20of%20projects%20if%20they%20haven't%20already.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20on%20your%20own%20projects%2C%20he%20said%2C%20could%20come%20in%20handy%20during%20interviews%20when%20employers%20want%20to%20see%20how%20candidates%20approach%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BContinuing%20one's%20education%20beyond%20school%2C%20whether%20formally%20or%20informally%2C%20forever%20expanding%20your%20own%20knowledge%20and%20skills%2C%20can%20certainly%20help%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20Malan%20said.%20%26quo