o%20inform%20him%20that%20his%20data%20was%20being%20sold%20to%20vendors%2C%20thereby%20allowing%20people%20outside%20the%20app%20to%20discover%20his%20presence%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBurrill's%20lawsuit%2C%20obtained%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fnation%2F2024%2F07%2F27%2Fpriest-grindr-privacy-lawsuit%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EWashington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20states%20that%20the%20release%20of%20his%20data%20caused%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20damage%26quot%3B%20to%20his%20reputation%2C%20particularly%20given%20his%20vow%20of%20celibacy%20as%20a%20priest%20and%20the%20Catholic%20Church's%20long-standing%20stance%20against%20homosexual%20acts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBurrill%20was%20forced%20to%20resign%20from%20his%20position%20after%20the%20Christian%20news%20website%20%26quot%3BThe%20Pillar%26quot%3B%20published%20a%20story%20exposing%20his%20visits%20to%20gay%20bars%20and%20use%20of%20the%20dating%20app%2C%20reporting%20that%20it%20had%20tracked%20and%20verified%20his%20behaviour%20using%20online%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20lawsuit%2C%20Burrill%20alleges%20that%20The%20Pillar%20obtained%20the%20data%20from%20Catholic%20Laity%20and%20Clergy%20for%20Renewal%20(CLCR)%2C%20a%20Christian%20non-profit%20organization%20that%20purchased%20data%20from%20queer%20dating%20apps%20to%20identify%20Church%20leaders%20using%20them%20in%20violation%20of%20their%20vows%2C%20implying%20that%20Grindr%20had%20sold%20the%20data%20to%20the%20organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20want%20answers%20so%20we%20can%20use%20that%20as%20a%20warning%20to%20other%20Grindr%20users%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Gregory%20Helmer%2C%20an%20attorney%20for%20Burrill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20priest%20said%20he'd%20never%20have%20joined%20the%20app%20had%20he%20known%20his%20data%20would%20be%20available%20to%20the%20public%2C%20according%20to%20the%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20have%20that%20decision%20forced%20out%20of%20your%20hands%20and%20into%20the%20public%20realm%20is%20reprehensible%2C%E2%80%9D%20James%20Carr%2C%20another%20attorney%20representing%20Burrill%2C%20told%20the%20Washington%20Post.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBurrill%2C%20who%20is%20still%20%26quot%3Bgetting%20on%20his%20feet%26quot%3B%20following%20the%20%26quot%3Bshame%20and%20embarrassment%26quot%3B%20of%20his%20outing%2C%20according%20to%20his%20lawyer%20Helmer%2C%20requested%20%245%20million%20in%20damages%20from%20Grindr%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Grindr%20declined%20his%20request%2C%20Burrill%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%20on%20July%2018%2C%20seeking%20damages%20and%20the%20implementation%20of%20policies%20to%20prevent%20user%20data%20from%20being%20publicly%20available%20without%20users'%20knowledge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGrindr%20told%20the%20Washington%20Post%20it%20would%20%26quot%3Brespond%20vigorously%20to%20these%20allegations%2C%20which%20are%20based%20on%20mischaracterizations%20of%20practices%20relating%20to%20user%20data%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20previously%20denied%20making%20user%20data%20publicly%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECLCR%20admitted%20to%20obtaining%20data%20from%20Grindr%20in%20the%20past%20to%20expose%20clergy%20members%20but%20claimed%20it%20did%20not%20provide%20any%20data%20to%20The%20Pillar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBurrill's%20ousting%20sparked%20widespread%20criticism%2C%20with%20many%20condemning%20The%20Pillar's%20use%20of%20data%20as%20dangerously%20homophobic.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722309180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Fp8kr9iv8_monsignor-jeffrey-burrill_625x300_30_July_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-priest-sues-grindr-after-he-was-outed-and-forced-to-step-down-6219691%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Burrill%20was%20forced%20to%20resign%20from%20his%20position%20after%20the%20Christian%20news%20website%20published%20a%20story%20exposing%20his%20visits%20to%20gay%20bars%20and%20use%20of