d%20with%20other%20actions%2C%20has%20helped%20lower%20the%20breakeven%20point%20to%20levels%20where%20Tesla%20can%20still%20generate%20positive%20cash%20flow%20at%20an%20enterprise%20level%2C%20even%20with%20EV%20capacity%20utilization%20at%2069%25%20last%20quarter%2C%26quot%3B%20Jonas%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Tesla's%20cost%20cutting%20measures%20should%20help%20protect%20the%20stock%20from%20potential%20downside%2C%20its%20%26quot%3Bcornering%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20ZEV-market%20will%20help%20drive%20further%20upside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ZEV%20market%20refers%20to%20the%20buying%20and%20selling%20of%20regulatory%20compliance%20credits%20for%20companies%20that%20don't%20produce%20enough%20electric%20vehicles%20based%20on%20government%20requirements.%20With%20Tesla%20only%20producing%20electric%20cars%2C%20they%20have%20plenty%20of%20credits%20to%20sell%20to%20other%20automakers%2C%20Morgan%20Stanley%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTesla%20recognized%20zero%20emission%20vehicle%20credit%20revenue%20equating%20to%20around%20%242k%2Funit%20in%20the%20quarter%2C%20more%20than%202x%20the%20recent%20run-rate.%20We%20believe%20as%20more%20legacy%20OEMs%20pull%20back%20on%20their%20EV%20plans%2C%20combined%20with%20increasingly%20stringent%20EPA%20standards%2C%20that%20Tesla%20may%20achieve%20an%20even%20more%20dominant%20position%20in%20the%20market%20for%20highly%20lucrative%20ZEV%20credits%20going%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20Jonas%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFord%20indicated%20in%20its%20recent%20quarterly%20earnings%20report%20that%20it%20entered%20into%20agreements%20to%20purchase%20%243.8%20billion%20worth%20of%20regulatory%20compliance%20credits%20in%20North%20America%20and%20Europe%2C%20and%20General%20Motors%20and%20Stellantis%20are%20likely%20to%20follow%20suit%2C%20according%20to%20the%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20anticipate%20other%20car%20companies%20such%20as%20GM%20and%20STLA%20may%20be%20wading%20more%20deeply%20into%20the%20ZEV%20market%20as